{
  "text": "Recent research shows that circadian clocks can play an important role in human regenerative processes that can be faster or slower than the biological day [CITATION_1] . UVB penetration of the skin is largely in the interfollicular epidermis where circadian cell gating is prominent [CITATION_2] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "1667758",
    "[CITATION_2]": "1667758"
